			<figcaption>Janus with TIPO</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src={fig('RouWei_wTIPO.png')} alt='RouWei with TIPO' />
			<figcaption>RouWei with TIPO</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src={fig('HDM_woTIPO.png')} alt='HDM without TIPO' />
			<figcaption>HDM without TIPO</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src={fig('Janus_woTIPO.png')} alt='Janus without TIPO' />
			<figcaption>Janus without TIPO</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src={fig('RouWei_woTIPO.png')} alt='RouWei without TIPO' />
			<figcaption>RouWei without TIPO</figcaption>
		</figure>
	</div>

	<div class='prompt-container'>
		<div class='prompt-box'>
			<strong>Prompt for images with TIPO</strong>
			<p>{promptWith}</p>
		</div>
		<div class='prompt-box'>
			<strong>Prompt for images without TIPO</strong>
			<p>{promptWithout}</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<p>
		Even state-of-the-art models often fail to accurately interpret and reflect factual
		relationships in prompts. When prompts are precisely followed, the resulting images can often
		be distorted or broken. This highlights a significant challenge in text-to-image generation:
		maintaining image quality while ensuring strict adherence to complex prompt details.
	</p>

